Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to move unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. This can occur even when the driver's foot is not on the accelerator pedal, making it difficult to control the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates without pedal application
the vehicle moves on its own
the vehicle takes off without warning.
